# Installing Fonts - Systemwide
#### Check what fonts are installed
```bash
fc-list
```
- In case not installed run 
```
sudo apt-get install fontconfig
```


Step 1
```bash
cd .local/share
```
- Install Powerline fonts on Ubuntu
[Powerline Repository - Docs]

At `.local/share` run:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/powerline/fonts.git --depth=1
```

```bash
cd fonts
```
Install 
```bash
./install.sh
```
Go to home 
```bash
cd $HOME
```

#### Make the font available Systemwide
```bash
sudo cp -r ~/.local/share/fonts/*.ttf /usr/share/fonts
```

```bash
sudo fc-cache -fv
```

Restart the system 
```bash
sudo reboot
```

After it the font will be available in the terminal to choose

# Trim command

```bash
vim trim
```

```bash
#!/bin/bash

input="$@"
trimmed=$(echo -n "$input" | sed -e 's/^[[:space:]]*//' -e 's/[[:space:]]*$//')
echo "$trimmed"
```

```bash
chmod +x trim
```

```bash
sudo mv trim /usr/bin
```

